(43, 1, '2012-08-15 09:48:25', '2012-08-15 09:48:25', 'Doc I know why I can’t lose weight it’s my metabolism.  How often have I heard these words? Thousands of times I have heard these words, but most physicians have no way to measure metabolism.\n\nAt Renew youth we are able to actually measure your basic metabolic rate (BMR). Very few facilities, mostly research institutions have that capability. This test is different than a thyroid test. Thyroid is one of the many factors that determine metabolism, but BMR is the sum of all factors that determine metabolism, including thyroid.\n\nThe test itself is simple. You breathe into a machine that measures your oxygen consumption over a 10 minute period. It is preferable that you not eat or consume caffeinated beverages for at least 3 hours prior to that test. Based upon the oxygen consumption, the machine can calculate the sum of all of your metabolic reactions during that period and determine your calorie consumption at rest! It will then compare that to other people your sex, age, height and weight and tell you where you stand metabolically.\n\nThe results can be surprising and for some disappointing. That denial excuse can be blown away. No I am sorry to tell you that your metabolism is above average, it’s the lack of exercise, skipping breakfast, and the ice cream that make you fat, not your metabolism. Well anyway, once we have the numbers, we can start to address the real problems, and if it is metabolism there are some interventions that can be recommended!\n\nMetabolic testing is available to all at a nominal charge, and is highly recommended for our weight loss paitients and included in anti-aging patients.\n\nTo be included with video of BMR or picture of someone doing BMR test', 'Metabolic <span>Testing</span>', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '12-autosave', '', '', '2012-08-15 09:48:25', '2012-08-15 09:48:25', '', 12, 'http://localhost/renew-youth/12-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
